Byasa mencius is a butterfly from the family Papilionidae (swallowtails). It is found in China. The species was first described by Cajetan Felder and Rudolf Felder in 1862.
The wingspan is 10â€“11 cm. The wings are dark brown with chain of large red spots on the hindwings. The underside of the body is covered in red hairs.The larvae feed on Cocullus carolinus.